article.headline: Indiana St. 54, Illinois St. 50
article.story: NORMAL, IL (AP) -- Jay Tunnell scored 13 points Saturday as Indiana State defeated Illinois State 54-50 in a game that featured seven ties and 18 lead changes. A jumper by Illinois State's Greg Dilligard tied the game at 49 with 2:33 remaining. But Adam Arnold hit a jump shot for the Sycamores with 1:38 left to give Indiana State a lead they would not relinquish. Arnold and Tunnell each made free throws in the final minute to insure the Sycamores of a victory. Arnold finished with nine points and eight rebounds for Indiana State (10-4, 3-1). The Sycamores won despite shooting 31.9 percent from the field, including 6-for-21 from 3-point range. Illinois State shot just 32.7 percent while making 4-of-24 3-point attempts. Levi Dyer led Illinois State (8-7, 0-4) with 11 points. Osiris Eldridge had nine points and eight rebounds for the Redbirds.
